s, but Samira ate only the peanuts in it and took the rest back home.\n“It was like wet sand,” she said when Amma asked her why she hadn’t eaten it.","words":[[50,"“I"],[51,"don’t"],[52,"like"],[53,"noodles.”"],[54,"The"],[55,"next"],[56,"day,"],[57,"Amma"],[58,"made"],[59,"upma"],[60,"with"],[61,"peanuts"],[62,"and"],[63,"peas,"],[64,"but"],[65,"Samira"],[66,"ate"],[67,"only"],[68,"the"],[69,"peanuts"],[70,"in"],[71,"it"],[72,"and"],[73,"took"],[74,"the"],[75,"rest"],[76,"back"],[77,"home."],[78,"“It"],[79,"was"],[80,"like"],[81,"wet"],[82,"sand,”"],[83,"she"],[84,"said"],[85,"when"],[86,"Amma"],[87,"asked"],[88,"her"],[89,"why"],[90,"she"],[91,"hadn’t"],[92,"eaten"],[93,"it."]]},{"n":3,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/11147/size6/240b6710c2331ea959faed81bf4cefd4.jpg","text":"“Shall I give you idlis?” asked Amma.\n“Oh, yes ! They would be lovely to play with. I can toss and catch them. But I will not eat them—idlis taste like mud.”\nSo now there were parathas and brinjal curry. Ugh, ugh, ugh!","words":[[94,"“Shall"],[95,"I"],[96,"give"],[97,"you"],[98,"idlis?”"],[99,"asked"],[100,"Amma."],[101,"“Oh,"],[102,"yes"],[103,"!"],[104,"They"],[105,"would"],[106,"be"],[107,"lovely"],[108,"to"],[109,"play"],[110,"with."],[111,"I"],[112,"can"],[113,"toss"],[114,"and"],[115,"catch"],[116,"them."],[117,"But"],[118,"I"],[119,"will"],[120,"not"],[121,"eat"],[122,"them—idlis"],[123,"taste"],[124,"like"],[125,"mud.”"],[126,"So"],[127,"now"],[128,"there"],[129,"were"],[130,"parathas"],[131,"and"],[132,"brinjal"],[133,"curry."],[134,"Ugh,"],[135,"ugh,"],[136,"ugh!"]]},{"n":4,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/11148/size6/2002c8327d1b6a814885e36f71b13df4.jpg","text":"Shutting her tiffin box with a bang, Samira went to the school courtyard. A row of ants crawling along the wall said, “Samira, why aren’t you eating your lunch like all the other children?”\nSamira said, “I don’t like parathas. I don’t like vegetables. I don’t want any lunch.”","words":[[137,"Shutting"],[138,"her"],[139,"tiffin"],[140,"box"],[141,"with"],[142,"a"],[143,"bang,"],[144,"Samira"],[145,"went"],[146,"to"],[147,"the"],[148,"school"],[149,"courtyard."],[150,"A"],[151,"row"],[152,"of"],[153,"ants"],[154,"crawling"],[155,"along"],[156,"the"],[157,"wall"],[158,"said,"],[159,"“Samira,"],[160,"why"],[161,"aren’t"],[162,"you"],[163,"eating"],[164,"your"],[165,"lunch"],[166,"like"],[167,"all"],[168,"the"],[169,"other"],[170,"children?”"],[171,"Samira"],[172,"said,"],[173,"“I"],[174,"don’t"],[175,"like"],[176,"parathas."],[177,"I"],[178,"don’t"],[179,"like"],[180,"vegetables."],[181,"I"],[182,"don’t"],[183,"want"],[184,"any"],[185,"lunch.”"]]},{"n":5,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/11149/size6/5aa7fb0d70f90a01cfa323efaba698cf.jpg","text":"“Of course, one cannot eat vegetables,” the ants agreed. They offered her the wing of a cockroach that they were carefully carrying and said, “Now try this, it is really delicious.”\n“Oh no! I don’t want any horrible cockroaches,” said Samira and ran away to the garden.","words":[[186,"“Of"],[187,"course,"],[188,"one"],[189,"cannot"],[190,"eat"],[191,"vegetables,”"],[192,"the"],[193,"ants"],[194,"agreed."],[195,"They"],[196,"offered"],[197,"her"],[198,"the"],[199,"wing"],[200,"of"],[201,"a"],[202,"cockroach"],[203,"that"],[204,"they"],[205,"were"],[206,"carefully"],[207,"carrying"],[208,"and"],[209,"said,"],[210,"“Now"],[211,"try"],[212,"this,"],[213,"it"],[214,"is"],[215,"really"],[216,"delicious.”"],[217,"“Oh"],[218,"no!"],[219,"I"],[220,"don’t"],[221,"want"],[222,"any"],[223,"horrible"],[224,"cockroaches,”"],[225,"said"],[226,"Samira"],[227,"and"],[228,"ran"],[229,"away"],[230,"to"],[231,"the"],[232,"garden."]]},{"n":6,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/11150/size6/9d20364de2f8dfe8b8855b8fc97daab1.jpg","text":"Colourful flowers were blooming in the g