 pipal tree in the lawn.","words":[[310,"Samira"],[311,"put"],[312,"her"],[313,"tongue"],[314,"into"],[315,"the"],[316,"centre"],[317,"of"],[318,"a"],[319,"flower"],[320,"but"],[321,"could"],[322,"find"],[323,"nothing!"],[324,"“I"],[325,"don’t"],[326,"want"],[327,"any"],[328,"nectar."],[329,"And"],[330,"I"],[331,"think"],[332,"you"],[333,"are"],[334,"fooling"],[335,"me,”"],[336,"she"],[337,"cried."],[338,"She"],[339,"ran"],[340,"to"],[341,"the"],[342,"big"],[343,"pipal"],[344,"tree"],[345,"in"],[346,"the"],[347,"lawn."]]},{"n":9,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/11153/size6/368d31222241c84e157658d15f7c2d97.jpg","text":"A crow cawing above called, “Hello Samira! Why aren’t you eating your lunch like all the other children?”\n \nSamira said, “I don’t like parathas. I don’t like vegetables. I don’t want any lunch.”","words":[[348,"A"],[349,"crow"],[350,"cawing"],[351,"above"],[352,"called,"],[353,"“Hello"],[354,"Samira!"],[355,"Why"],[356,"aren’t"],[357,"you"],[358,"eating"],[359,"your"],[360,"lunch"],[361,"like"],[362,"all"],[363,"the"],[364,"other"],[365,"children?”"],[366,"Samira"],[367,"said,"],[368,"“I"],[369,"don’t"],[370,"like"],[371,"parathas."],[372,"I"],[373,"don’t"],[374,"like"],[375,"vegetables."],[376,"I"],[377,"don’t"],[378,"want"],[379,"any"],[380,"lunch.”"]]},{"n":10,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/11154/size6/fde844b79e0dc8955ddbc1b0dbacf1ec.jpg","text":"“Of course, one cannot eat vegetables,” the crow agreed, “Here, I’ll give you something nice,” and it dropped a half-eaten mouse for Samira.\n“Oh no! What a terrible thing! Keep your mouse for yourself,” screamed Samira and ran away to stand near the wall.","words":[[381,"“Of"],[382,"course,"],[383,"one"],[384,"cannot"],[385,"eat"],[386,"vegetables,”"],[387,"the"],[388,"crow"],[389,"agreed,"],[390,"“Here,"],[391,"I’ll"],[392,"give"],[393,"you"],[394,"something"],[395,"nice,”"],[396,"and"],[397,"it"],[398